===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|automatique|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|αὐτόματον|lang=grc}}, neuter of {{term|αὐτόματος||self-moving, moving of oneself, self-acting, spontaneous|lang=grc}}, from {{term|αὐτός||self, myself|lang=grc}} + {{term|μέμαα||to wish eagerly, strive, yearn, desire|lang=grc}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˌɔːtəˈmætɪk/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˌɔtəˈmætɪk/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-automatic.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ætɪk|lang=en}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Capable of operating without external [[control]] or [[intervention]].
#: ''The '''automatic''' clothes washer was a great labor-saving device''
# Done out of [[habit]] or without [[conscious]] thought.
#: ''The reaction was '''automatic''': flight!''
# {{context|of a [[firearm]] such as a [[machine gun]]|lang=en}} Firing continuously as long as the [[trigger]] is pressed until [[ammunition]] is exhausted.
# {{context|computing|of a local [[variable]]|lang=en}} Automatically added to and removed from the [[stack]] during the course of [[function]] [[call]]s.
# {{context|maths|of a group|lang=en}} Having one or more finite-state [[automata]]

